---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Your Name" description="About the photographer">
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-4xl text-white mb-8">About</h1>

    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-12">
      <div class="md:w-1/3 shrink-0">
        <div class="aspect-square bg-stone-900 flex items-center justify-center text-stone-500 text-sm">
          Portrait placeholder
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="md:w-2/3 space-y-5 text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          This is where your story goes. Who you are, what draws you to photography,
          and what you're trying to capture. Keep it personal — people connect with
          the person behind the camera.
        </p>
        <p>
          Maybe mention how cycling informs the way you see landscapes, or how
          moving through a place at a different speed changes what you notice.
        </p>
        <p>
          You could talk about your gear, your process, the places you keep
          returning to, or what you're working on next.
        </p>

        <div class="pt-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
          <h2 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-xl text-white mb-4">Get in touch</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-400">
            You can reach me at
            <a href="mailto:hello@example.com" class="text-white hover:text-stone-300 transition-colors underline underline-offset-4">
              hello@example.com
            </a>
            or find me on
            <a href="https://instagram.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-white hover:text-stone-300 transition-colors underline underline-offset-4">
              Instagram
            </a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>